<subSubSection id="9E82650CFFBDFFB6E3ACF96FFEA44EE7" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBDFFB7E3ACF96FFD5C482B" blockId="12.[136,1452,1638,1840]" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBDFFB7E3ACF96FFF7E4810" bold="true" box="[136,235,1782,1803]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:—Ab aliis subspeciebus Hieracii prenanthoidis foliis caulinis brevibus, pilis glandulosis pedunculorum involucrique praecipue brevibus, pilis stellatis involucri modice densis differt.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBDFFB7E3ACF8C7FE7648FF" blockId="12.[136,1452,1886,2093]" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">
Perennial, rhizome stout, vertical. Stem erect, vertical, cylindrical, stout, basin subligneous (Ø 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBDFFB7E7FCF8C7FAA94862" box="[1240,1340,1886,1913]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
), (55)60– 75(80) cm tall, reddish green, brownish-purple at the base, striated, aphyllopodous, in the lower part with sparse, in the upper part with moderate, 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBDFFB7E289F83FFD8A48DA" box="[429,543,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
long, whitish, soft, simple hairs, in the upper part additionally with sparse stellate and occasional glandular hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBDFFB6E399F877FD8D4E1B" blockId="12.[136,1452,1886,2093]" lastBlockId="13.[136,1452,158,1085]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="12" pageNumber="51">
Cauline leaves (13)15–20(25), in the lower third mostly withered at anthesis, 2–8 × 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBDFFB7E749F877FB564712" box="[1133,1219,2030,2057]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" unit="cm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 cm</quantity>
, the lower ones long attenuate, cordate at base, elliptical, entire, acute, upper surface green or dark green, with sparse 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBDFFB7E7EDF78BFAB34736" box="[1225,1318,2066,2093]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long white, soft simple hairs, lower surface greyish green, margins and vein of the lower surface with moderate sparse simple white hairs 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBCFFB6E3E3FF5BFEB34FC6" box="[199,294,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long, the other stem leaves gradually decreasing in size upwards, semiamplexicaul at base, indument similar to those of the lower leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBCFFB6E399FE93FAB34E77" blockId="13.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
Synflorescence laxly paniculate, branches (5)7–9(11), spreading, 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBCFFB6E088FE93FB854E3E" box="[940,1040,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" unit="cm" value="6.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.0">3–10 cm</quantity>
long, each with (1)2–5(7) capitula; capitula (10)15–30(40); acladium 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBCFFB6E12FFEB7FDE04E52" box="[523,629,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–3 cm</quantity>
long. Peduncles with 2–3 linear, dark, olive green bracts, 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBCFFB6E628FEB7FAFE4E52" box="[1292,1387,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long, with numerous stellate and glandular hairs, the latter only 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBCFFB6E030FECBFC0E4E76" box="[788,923,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
long, yellow, without simple hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBCFFB6E399FEEFFEA44EE7" blockId="13.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
Involucre campanulate, 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBCFFB6E2E8FEEFFDBC4E8A" box="[460,553,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9 mm</quantity>
long. Involucral bracts in a few series, olive green, linear-lanceolate, 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBCFFB6E61DFEEFFA394E8A" box="[1337,1452,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1 mm</quantity>
wide, acute, with numerous yellow, 0.2–0.3 long glandular hairs, stellate hairs moderate, numerous along margins. Corolla limb ligulate, yellow, indistinctly ciliate. Styles blackish. Margins of alveoli ciliate. Achenes 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBCFFB6E62FFE27FAFF4EC2" box="[1291,1386,446,473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long, reddish brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E82650CFFBCFFB6E399FD9FFD424D5F" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBCFFB6E399FD9FFCFB4D3B" blockId="13.[136,1452,158,1085]" box="[189,878,518,545]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E399FD9FFEAB4D3B" bold="true" box="[189,318,518,544]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The subspecies epithet refers to Mount Penice.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBCFFB6E399FDB3FD424D5F" blockId="13.[136,1452,158,1085]" box="[189,727,554,580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E399FDB3FED64D5F" bold="true" box="[189,323,554,580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Phenology:</emphasis>
—Flowering and fruiting in August.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E82650CFFBCFFB6E399FDD7FC414C5B" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBCFFB6E399FDD7FEB94DAB" blockId="13.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E399FDD7FE7F4D73" bold="true" box="[189,490,590,616]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E129FDD6FC624D73" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" box="[525,1015,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="penicense">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E129FDD6FCBB4D73" box="[525,814,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Hieracium prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E0ADFDD6FC624D73" box="[905,1015,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">penicense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from Mount Penice. It grows on meadows, on margins of planted conifer woods and rocky slopes along the road to the summit of Mount Penice.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBCFFB6E399FD23FC414C5B" blockId="13.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E399FD23FE254DCF" bold="true" box="[189,432,698,724]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Conservation status</emphasis>
:—There are no ongoing threats acting on 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E096FD22FA314DCF" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" box="[946,1444,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="penicense">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E096FD22FB434DCF" box="[946,1238,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Hieracium prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E612FD22FA314DCF" box="[1334,1444,699,724]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">penicense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the roadside mowing has a negative impact on those plants that grow close to the road. Due to its restricted range and limited number of mature individuals (around 1,000), 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E07DFC9AFB494C07" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" box="[857,1244,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="penicense">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E07DFC9AFB8F4C07" box="[857,1050,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">H. prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E74AFC9AFB494C07" box="[1134,1244,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">penicense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could preliminary be listed as “Near Threatened” (NT) according to the IUCN criteria (2019).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E82650CFFBCFFB6E399FCD3FBE54B27" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBCFFB6E399FCD3FBE54B27" blockId="13.[136,1452,158,1085]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E399FCD3FEBF4C7F" bold="true" box="[189,298,842,868]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Remarks</emphasis>
:—The collective species 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E171FCD2FBD94C7E" authority="Villars (1779: 35)" authorityName="Villars" authorityPageNumber="35" authorityYear="1779" box="[597,1100,842,869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="prenanthoides">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E171FCD2FCE34C7F" box="[597,886,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Hieracium prenanthoides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B2094B76FFBCFFB6E0A4FCD3FBD94C7E" author="Villars, D." box="[896,1100,842,869]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" refId="ref8961" refString="Villars, D. (1779) Prospectus de l'histoire des plantes de Dauphine. Imprimerie Royale, Grenoble, 56 pp." type="book" year="1779">Villars (1779: 35)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has a widespread but disjunct range throughout Europe (map see 
<bibRefCitation id="B2094B76FFBCFFB6E136FCF7FD5D4C93" author="Brautigam, S." box="[530,712,878,904]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="325 - 333" refId="ref6745" refString="Brautigam, S. (1992) Hieracium. In: Meusel, H. &amp; Jager, E. J. (Eds.) Vergleichende Chorologie der zentraleuropaischen Flora, Bd. 3. G. Fischer, Jena, Stuttgart, New York, pp. 152 - 158, 192 - 193, 325 - 333 (text), 550 - 560 (maps)." type="journal article" year="1992">Bräutigam 1992</bibRefCitation>
) and Asia. More than 50 subspecies/microspecies were described. Except for some widespread taxa, i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E10FFC0AFB744CB7" authority="(Froel.) Fries (1862: 120)" authorityName="Fries" authorityPageNumber="120" authorityYear="1862" baseAuthorityName="Froel." box="[555,1249,914,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="perfoliatum">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E10FFC0AFD7F4CB7" box="[555,746,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">H. prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E018FC0BFC2A4CB7" box="[828,959,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">perfoliatum</emphasis>
(Froel.) 
<bibRefCitation id="B2094B76FFBCFFB6E73BFC0BFB744CB7" author="Fries, E." box="[1055,1249,914,940]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 158" refId="ref7462" refString="Fries, E. (1862) Epicrisis generis Hieraciorum. Uppsala Universitets Arsskrift 1862: 1 - 158." type="journal article" year="1862">Fries (1862: 120)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E7CFFC0AFD214CCA" authority="(Tausch) Zahn (1921: 751)" authorityName="Zahn" authorityPageNumber="751" authorityYear="1921" baseAuthorityName="Tausch" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="bupleurifolium">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E7CFFC0AFA3E4CB7" box="[1259,1451,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">H. prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E3F2FC2FFEE94CCB" box="[214,380,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">bupleurifolium</emphasis>
(Tausch) 
<bibRefCitation id="B2094B76FFBCFFB6E2C9FC2FFD214CCA" author="Zahn, K. H." box="[493,692,950,977]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="577 - 864" refId="ref9103" refString="Zahn, K. H. (1921) Compositae - Hieracium. In: Engler, H. G. A. (Ed.) Das Pflanzenreich, vol. 77. Engelmann, Leipzig, pp. 577 - 864." type="book chapter" year="1921">Zahn (1921: 751)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E1E4FC2EFA1C4CCA" authority="(Vill.) Zahn (1901: 1864)" authorityName="Zahn" authorityPageNumber="1864" authorityYear="1901" baseAuthorityName="Vill." box="[704,1417,950,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="lanceolatum">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E1E4FC2EFC174CCB" box="[704,898,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">H. prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E0FCFC2FFBF74CCB" box="[984,1122,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">lanceolatum</emphasis>
(Vill.) Zahn (1901: 1864)
</taxonomicName>
, in the outer alpine 
<collectingCountry id="AE8F7617FFBCFFB6E265FC43FEE14CEF" box="[321,372,986,1012]" name="Italy" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Italy</collectingCountry>
there are also some remarkable endemic taxa as 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E087FC42FF574B03" authority="Furrer &amp; Zahn" authorityName="Furrer &amp; Zahn" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="lissocorium">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E087FC42FBF04CEF" box="[931,1125,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">H. prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E799FC43FAD54CEF" box="[1213,1344,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">lissocorium</emphasis>
Furrer &amp; Zahn
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="B2094B76FFBCFFB6E3C6FC66FE254B03" author="Furrer, E." box="[226,432,1022,1049]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="225 - 233" refId="ref7482" refString="Furrer, E. (1929) Abruzzesische Hieracien. Vierteljahrsschrift der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft in Zurich 74: 225 - 233." type="journal article" year="1929">Furrer (1929: 232)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E2C7FC66FB324B03" authority="Gottschlich (2009: 133)" authorityName="Gottschlich" authorityPageNumber="133" authorityYear="2009" box="[483,1191,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="stupposifolium">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E2C7FC66FD364B03" box="[483,675,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">H. prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E1D1FC67FC0F4B03" box="[757,922,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">stupposifolium</emphasis>
Gottschlich (2009: 133)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion id="145CF865FFBCFFB6E7E3FC67FABE4B03" box="[1223,1323,1022,1048]" country="Italy" name="Abruzzo" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Abruzzo</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBCFFB6E610FC66FE7F4B27" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="prenanthoides" subSpecies="penicense">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E610FC66FEB24B27" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Hieracium prenanthoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBCFFB6E258FBBAFE7F4B27" box="[380,490,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">penicense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a further example of a local endemic in the Apennines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
